message:
@MikeDerk  I had the same problem. I can't see Christopher (or should I say the Alien?) as protagonist. He's just not a big enough part of the story until the end.

Perhaps he issue here is that everyone, apart from Wikus has some other objective than the one we are told about. MNU leads the relocation but actually cares about the weapons. The warlord trades cat food but really wants to be able to use the weapons, the aliens appear stupid and disoriented but then one of them is developing high technology to get back to the mother ship, the soldier's task appears to be to defend Wikus and his team but in reality he just wants to kill aliens.

Should we be focusing on what the film led us to believe was true, or what was actually true?
